Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Halve any large @cauliflower florets{300%g}.

Pop the cauliflower onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread them out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the cauliflower cooks, zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2} as thinly as you can.

Pop the onion into a #small bowl{} and add half the lime juice and @sugar{1%tsp} for the pickle. Add a pinch of salt, mix together and set aside to pickle.

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks.

Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the sweetcorn, tomato chunks, lime zest, remaining lime juice and the @sugar{1%tsp} for the salsa. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

In another small bowl, combine the @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and the @honey{1%tbsp}.

When the cauli has ~{5%minutes} of cooking remaining, pour over the chipotle mixture and toss to coat the florets evenly. Return to the oven for the remaining cook time.

When everything's nearly ready, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} (3 per person) onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, put the tortillas onto your plates and spread a spoonful of the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} over each one.

Divide the @wild rocket{20%g}, chorizo and chipotle roasted cauliflower between the tortillas and top with spoonfuls of the tomato salsa.

Finish with the pickled onions and crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} over the top. Enjoy!